  "prompt": "Does the warranty on the car electrical wiring lapse in case one gets a music system fitted from outside and not from the company showroom?",
  "response": "The warranty on your car's electrical wiring can indeed lapse if you get a music system fitted from outside rather than from the company showroom. Car manufacturers often have strict guidelines regarding aftermarket modifications. Using third-party service providers or non-approved parts can lead to warranty voidance, especially if the modification affects the electrical system or causes damage.\n\nIt's advisable to check with your car manufacturer or consult the warranty documentation to understand the specifics of your warranty coverage. Some manufacturers might allow certain modifications if performed by certified technicians or if the parts meet specific standards, but it's best to confirm this to avoid any issues with warranty claims in the future.",
